  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Leaflet</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1947 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The leaflet features a framed collage of two photographs. The background picture shows a young woman with her hair in bunches, wearing a bow and a dress with a wide white collar. She is holding a bunch of flowers in her left hand. The smaller picture in the foreground shows a young smiling woman in the centre of about the same age and with a similar hairstyle. She is surrounded by ten schoolboys and girls wearing school uniforms. They are looking at her with expressions of admiration. The film title in Serbo-Croatian, ‘Seoska učiteljica’ (in the Russian original: ‘Сельская учительница’, The village teacher), as well as an indication of the film’s Soviet origin, are displayed in a white field in the centre of the picture.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The film was directed by Марк Донской (Mark Donskoy) and released in 1947.</ab>
